## <a id='apps-man'></a> Apps Manager Highlights

Apps Manager v<%= vars.current_major_version %> includes the following important major features:

### <a id='async-bindings'></a> Support for Asynchronous Bindings

Apps Manager supports asynchronous bindings. Asynchronous bindings help avoid timeouts for synchronous operations in PAS by allowing service brokers more time to complete a bind.

For more information about managing apps with Apps Manager, see [Managing Apps and Service Instances Using Apps Manager](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/console/manage-apps.html).

## <a id='platform-automation'></a> Platform Automation Highlights

Platform Automation includes the following important major features:

### <a id='platform-automation-ga'></a> Platform Automation for PCF is Generally Available

Platform Automation for PCF uses a command line utility for working with Ops Manager called Om, Concourse tasks, and example pipelines to help operators create an automated pipeline for installing and upgrading their PCF foundations.

For more information about Platform Automation for PCF, see the [Platform Automation for PCF documentation](http://docs.pivotal.io/platform-automation).

For more information about working with Om, see [Om](https://github.com/pivotal-cf/om) on GitHub.
